<br>
Intent: To get the Chardok pipe for Targys and Zirknom.  This is the last piece of the Robe of the Whistling Fist - which must be turned in to start the monk epic.<br>
<br>
Where:  Meet outside the Sarnak fort in the NE corner of Burning Woods - stay far enough away from the fort and watch for wanderers.<br>
<br>
When: 1/12/01 1pm EST (Saturday)<br>
<br>
Group(s) needed: ONE group of 54+ ... OR ... TWO groups of 50+ each consisting of:<br>
<br>
Enchanter<br>
Cleric<br>
Monk (duh!)<br>
Druid<br>
melee (Warrior prefered, SK, Pally, Ranger)<br>
other (if warrior then thruely anything else, if no warrior then Rogue<br>
<br>
This can be more fluid but caster types are dangerous  in the cramped quarters of Chardok unless in *real* large raids.<br>
<br>
Discription:  From zone in we have two options:<br>
1) Go into the guard house, to the first bridge, below the bridge, fighting our way to make camp in the Captain's Room (this is the most direct route)<br>
2) Go to zone out, levitate everyone, &quot;fly&quot; to the tunnel above the floor, fighting our way to make camp in the Captains Room<br>
Both are tough options, the Captain is lvl56, hits for 160s <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
- the spawn time in Chardok is roughly 26 miniutes, once we kill we must move<br>
***** the Iksar Betrayer is a rare spawn, so EXPECT to be there for a few hours for both monks, he ALWAYS drops the piece and is a 57 monk himself, hits for 170s, he and his PHs are on a 16 minute timer<br>
<br>
I encourage EVERYONE who can go to study the map link:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://hon.museek.com/images/takko/betrayer.jpg">hon.museek.com/images/takko/betrayer.jpg</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
I guarantee this will be tough - holding the camp is the real challenge.. but it can be done.<br>
<br>
All loot is CAWU random roll for multi class items, 50% of cash will go to clerics for spell components.. the rest goes to the guild.<br>
<br>
CR plan: with a druid in each group we should not get wiped out.  MA will call for evac... we will only get two attempts (i.e one raid evac).  Then the raid will be attempted another time.  In case of a wipe-out... well, this is my first time organizing a raid... you post here for suggestions <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
